 \"r=2\", \"r=5\", \"r=10\"]);" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 
204 "" 0 "" {TEXT 209 0 "" }}{PARA 204 "" 0 "" {TEXT 209 104 "The plot
 reveals that there are two saddle-node bifurcations: the \"birth\" of
 x3, and the \"decease\" of x1" }{TEXT 209 0 "" }}{PARA 204 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT 209 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 208 "" 0 "" {TEXT 213 0 "" }}{PARA 208 
"" 0 "" {TEXT 213 22 "e) bifurcations points" }}{PARA 208 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT 213 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 204 "" 0 "" {TEXT 209 110 "At bifurcati
on the stability of the fixed point is marginal; so there are two equa
tions that must be satisfied" }{TEXT 209 0 "" }}{PARA 204 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT 209 50 "f(x,r)=0 (to be a fixed point) and df/dx(x,r) = 0 " }
{TEXT 209 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 202 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 14 "eq1 := f
(x)=0;" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 202 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 
17 "eq2 := df(x) = 0;" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 204 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT 209 30 "we manipulate a bit to obtain:" }{TEXT 209 0 "" }}}
{EXCHG {PARA 202 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 31 "eq3 := simplify(2*x*eq1 + \+
eq2);" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 202 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 
21 "sols := solve(eq3,x);" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 202 "> "
 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 15 "xc1 := sols[1];" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}{EXCHG 
{PARA 202 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 15 "xc2 := sols[2];" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 0 
"" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 202 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 11 "evalf(xc2);" }
{MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 204 "" 0 "" {TEXT 209 83 "This prove
s the value of the fixed points at bifurcation. Now the critical r val
ues" }{TEXT 209 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 202 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 24 "r1
 := solve(f(xc1)=0,r);" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 202 "> " 0 
"" {MPLTEXT 1 0 10 "evalf(r1);" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 
202 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 24 "r2 := solve(f(xc2)=0,r);" }{MPLTEXT 1 
